<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 108 (3) of the Financial Regulation of 21 December 1977 applicable to the general budget of the European Communities (1), as amended by Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 1252/79 (2), the appropriations made available by a decision taken in accordance with the second subparagraph of paragraph 2 or because the beneficiary abandons the project or reduces the investments laid down in the decision to grant aid, may be used for the financing of other projects. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks Euroopa &uuml;henduste &uuml;ldeelarve suhtes kohaldatava 21. detsembri 1977. aasta finantsm&auml;&auml;ruse (9) (muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, EURATOM) nr 1252/79 (10)) artikli 108 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaldamist, v&otilde;ib assigneeringuid, mis on vabanenud l&otilde;ike 2 teise l&otilde;igu kohaselt tehtud otsuse alusel v&otilde;i seet&otilde;ttu, et abisaaja on projektist loobunud v&otilde;i abiandmisotsusega etten&auml;htud investeeringuid v&auml;hendanud, kasutada muude projektide finantseerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> The particulars which applications for aid from the Fund referred to in Article 8 must contain and the form in which projects must be presented are those set out in Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1898/80 (3). </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;ksikasjad, mida artiklis 8 osutatud fondist abi saamise taotlused peavad sisaldama, ning projektide esitamise vorm on s&auml;testatud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1898/80. (11) </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the procedure laid down in this Article is to be followed, the matter shall be referred to the Standing Committee for the Fishing Industry, either on the initiative of its chairman or at the request of the representative of a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tuleb j&auml;rgida k&auml;esolevas artiklis s&auml;testatud korda, suunab kalamajanduse alalise komitee eesistuja k&uuml;simuse omal algatusel v&otilde;i liikmesriigi esindaja taotluse korral komiteele. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The representative of the Commission shall submit a draft of the measures to be taken. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni esindaja esitab v&otilde;etavate meetmete eeln&otilde;u. </eesti>
<inglise> The Committee shall deliver its opinion within a time limit to be set by the chairman according to the urgency of the matter. </inglise>
<eesti> Komitee esitab oma arvamuse t&auml;htaja jooksul, mille eesistuja m&auml;&auml;rab vastavalt k&uuml;simuse kiireloomulisusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Opinions shall be adopted by a majority of 45 votes, the votes of Member States being weighted in accordance with Article 148 (2) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> Arvamused v&otilde;etakse vastu 45-h&auml;&auml;lelise h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega, kusjuures liikmesriikide esindajate h&auml;&auml;li arvestatakse asutamislepingu artikli 148 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud viisil. </eesti>
<inglise> The chairman shall not vote. </inglise>
<eesti> Eesistuja ei h&auml;&auml;leta. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall adopt the measures, which shall apply immediately. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;tab meetmed vastu ning neid kohaldatakse viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise> However, if they are not in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee for the Fishing Industry, the Commission shall forthwith communicate them to the Council; in that event the Commission may defer their application for not more than one month from the date of such communication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui need meetmed ei ole koosk&otilde;las kalamajanduse alalise komitee arvamusega, teatab komisjon sellest viivitamata n&otilde;ukogule; sellisel juhul v&otilde;ib komisjon meetmete kohaldamise edasi l&uuml;kata kuni &uuml;he kuu v&otilde;rra alates k&otilde;nealuse teatamise kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council, acting by a qualified majority, may adopt different measures within one month. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;ib kvalifitseeritud h&auml;&auml;lteenamusega v&otilde;tta &uuml;he kuu jooksul vastu teistsuguse otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
